18/09/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia -- US Ambassador to Belgrade Michael Polt and Serbia's Minister for Foreign Economic Relations Milan Parivodic sealed a $15m agreement Friday (15 September), under which the US bought 4 hectares of land for the construction of a new embassy building in Belgrade.
Polt said that an additional $100m would be spent on construction and equipment over the next five years and up to 500 jobs would be created.
(Politika - 17/09/06;
Blic - 16/09/06)
